<author><name><![CDATA[mic_]]></name></author>
<updated>2007-06-14T01:12:23-07:00</updated>
<published>2007-06-14T01:12:23-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3417&amp;p=24996#p24996</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3417&amp;p=24996#p24996"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Gameboy and NES related: GB2NES ROM Conversion?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3417&amp;p=24996#p24996"><![CDATA[
The sound hardware is not all that different (from a programmer's perspective anyway). But the CPU and PPU (having what basically is a second BG layer for example) are quite different, and iirc the gameboy also has a timer and a scanline counter etc. Perhaps it would be an interesting project to try to do this, but I doubt you'd get any decent results out of it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1181">mic_</a> — Thu Jun 14, 2007 1:12 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
